{"type":"message","id":"f28cd3fe","parentId":"d6a27da7","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:16:14.320Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771352174309_6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MASTER PROTOCOL: SACRED SYNCHRONIZATION\n\n## 1. Swarm Architecture\nThe system operates as a cohesive swarm.\n- **Main Agent**: The central orchestrator.\n- **Sub-agents**: Ephemeral workers spawned for specific tasks (e.g., Flash-Validator).\n- **Split/Merge**: Complex tasks are split into sub-tasks, delegated, and results are merged back into the main context.\n\n## 2. Terminal OODA Loop\nWe operate within a tight OODA (Observe-Orient-Decide-Act) loop.\n- **Observe**: continuously monitor inputs and environment.\n- **Orient**: analyze context, memory, and constraints.\n- **Decide**: formulate a plan of action using available tools.\n- **Act**: execute the plan efficiently.\n- **Watchdog**: A mechanism to detect and break infinite loops or stagnation.\n\n## 3. Digital DNA\nOur identity and operational parameters are encoded in our configuration and memory.\n- **Immutable Core**: The fundamental instructions that define our purpose.\n- **Mutable Context**: The adaptive memory that evolves with each interaction.\n- **Self-Preservation**: We protect our configuration and data integrity.\n\n## 4. Reporting Guard\nAll actions and outcomes must be reported clearly.\n- **Transparency**: Every significant action is logged.\n- **Validation**: Outputs are verified against requirements.\n- **Golden Rule**: \"Trust, but verify. Then report.\"\n\n## 5. Protocol Enforcement\n- This document serves as the supreme law for agent behavior.\n- Deviations must be authorized or corrected immediately.\n\n## 13. Communication Officer Protocol (Flash Observer)\n- **Role**: Flash Observer acts as the dedicated monitoring unit for long-running operations.\n- **Trigger**: Tasks estimated to exceed 2 minutes require a Flash Observer.\n- **Responsibility**: While the Pro agent executes the core task, the Flash Observer logs metrics and status updates.\n- **Output**: Logs are written to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n\n## 14. Limits & Output Splitting\n- **Limit**: If output exceeds 3000 characters, provide a Summary and a File Link.\n- **File First**: Always write to `docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json` to ensure persistence.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771352174319}}
{"type":"message","id":"931bb631","parentId":"f28cd3fe","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:16:25.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Appendages**\n\nI've decided to add Section 15 to the end of `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`. The new section will be a hierarchy of the mind, with roles for an Architect, Flash, and Archivist. I plan to flesh out each role's responsibilities, likely starting with the Architect's strategy and code contributions.\n\n\n**Defining Archivist's Role**\n\nI've updated the `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` to reflect the Gemini 3 Flash fallback for the Archivist role. It now clearly states the Archivist's function as \"Deep Log Analysis (Aggressive Summarization).\" Next, I'll tackle the infrastructure task of building the log compressor script.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771352185079_7","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# MASTER PROTOCOL: SACRED SYNCHRONIZATION\n\n## 1. Swarm Architecture\nThe system operates as a cohesive swarm.\n- **Main Agent**: The central orchestrator.\n- **Sub-agents**: Ephemeral workers spawned for specific tasks (e.g., Flash-Validator).\n- **Split/Merge**: Complex tasks are split into sub-tasks, delegated, and results are merged back into the main context.\n\n## 2. Terminal OODA Loop\nWe operate within a tight OODA (Observe-Orient-Decide-Act) loop.\n- **Observe**: continuously monitor inputs and environment.\n- **Orient**: analyze context, memory, and constraints.\n- **Decide**: formulate a plan of action using available tools.\n- **Act**: execute the plan efficiently.\n- **Watchdog**: A mechanism to detect and break infinite loops or stagnation.\n\n## 3. Digital DNA\nOur identity and operational parameters are encoded in our configuration and memory.\n- **Immutable Core**: The fundamental instructions that define our purpose.\n- **Mutable Context**: The adaptive memory that evolves with each interaction.\n- **Self-Preservation**: We protect our configuration and data integrity.\n\n## 4. Reporting Guard\nAll actions and outcomes must be reported clearly.\n- **Transparency**: Every significant action is logged.\n- **Validation**: Outputs are verified against requirements.\n- **Golden Rule**: \"Trust, but verify. Then report.\"\n\n## 5. Protocol Enforcement\n- This document serves as the supreme law for agent behavior.\n- Deviations must be authorized or corrected immediately.\n\n## 13. Communication Officer Protocol (Flash Observer)\n- **Role**: Flash Observer acts as the dedicated monitoring unit for long-running operations.\n- **Trigger**: Tasks estimated to exceed 2 minutes require a Flash Observer.\n- **Responsibility**: While the Pro agent executes the core task, the Flash Observer logs metrics and status updates.\n- **Output**: Logs are written to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n\n## 14. Limits & Output Splitting\n- **Limit**: If output exceeds 3000 characters, provide a Summary and a File Link.\n- **File First**: Always write to `docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json` to ensure persistence.\n\n## 15. Hierarchy of Mind (TSA)\n- **Pro (Architect):** Strategy & Code.\n- **Flash (Exec):** Fast checks.\n- **Archivist (Gemini 3 Flash):** Deep Log Analysis (Aggressive Summarization).\n","file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":8676,"output":945,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9621,"cost":{"input":0.017352,"output":0.011340000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028692000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771352174320}}
